NAME
    who(1)		- who is currently on the system

SYNOPSIS
    who  [  user  |  device  |  am i  ]

DESCRIPTION
    If no options are given then who(1) displays the name,
    terminal port and log-in time for all of the present
    users.

    A "user" or "device" name checks for a current log-in
    by the "user" or at the "device". If two arguments are
    given then who(1) only reports on the current session.

FILES
    /usr/adm/wtmp

SEE ALSO
    last(1), whoami(1)
